abstract: The author of “Far From the Tree” loves reading Virginia Woolf, but in small portions. “I could easily become emotionally obese if I let myself consume her work too often.”

abstract: The Moscow Biennale of Contemporary Art steers cautiously between its ambition to promote that city as a cutting-edge art center and a concern about drawing the wrath of officialdom.
snippet: The Moscow Biennale of Contemporary Art steers cautiously between its ambition to promote that city as a cutting-edge art center and a concern about drawing the wrath of officialdom.
lead_paragraph: MOSCOW — There were some complications when the Conceptual artist John Baldessari brought his latest works to Russia as part of the fifth Moscow Biennale of Contemporary Art. First, the title of his project, “Double Take,” did not translate easily into Russian.

abstract: The Tea Party helped cost Democrats control of the House in 2010, but its political energy can put Republicans in difficult positions, too.
snippet: The Tea Party helped cost Democrats control of the House in 2010, but its political energy can put Republicans in difficult positions, too.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The extraordinary zeal of the Tea Party has been a signature development during Barack Obama’s presidency — with dangers for both Republicans and Democrats.

abstract: Speaker John A. Boehner surrendered to demands that he tie money to keep the government open after Sept. 30 to stripping President Obama’s health care law of any financing.
snippet: Speaker John A. Boehner surrendered to demands that he tie money to keep the government open after Sept. 30 to stripping President Obama’s health care law of any financing.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — After three years of cajoling, finessing and occasionally strong-arming his fitful conservative majority, Speaker John A. Boehner waved the white flag on Wednesday, surrendering to demands from his right flank that he tie money to keep the government open after Sept. 30 to stripping President Obama’s health care law of any financing.

abstract: After decades of buying cars and never selling them, an elderly owner of a Nebraska General Motors dealership is finally getting rid of his now-prodigious collection.
snippet: After decades of buying cars and never selling them, an elderly owner of a Nebraska General Motors dealership is finally getting rid of his now-prodigious collection.
lead_paragraph: PIERCE, Neb. — Unless you happen to be headed to Plainview, Neb., the world’s “Klown Kapital,” the small town of Pierce (population 1,700) isn’t on the way to anywhere. You have to jog off the main four-lane (U.S. 81) and take a state road northwest, past farms and fields, and then more farms and fields.

abstract: The exhibition, which opens Saturday, planned to focus on public spaces long before the angry protests in May about how the government was developing the city.
snippet: The exhibition, which opens Saturday, planned to focus on public spaces long before the angry protests in May about how the government was developing the city.
lead_paragraph: ISTANBUL — Back in January, Fulya Erdemci, the curator of this year’s Istanbul Biennial, decided to focus the exhibition on art in public spaces. The city was booming, but at what cost, and for whose benefit? It had become the central question there. Ms. Erdemci wanted artists to engage with the issue, and citizens to engage with public art.

abstract: The San Blas Islands, off the coast of Panama, may not offer your average Caribbean escape. But, that may be exactly why you’d want to go.
snippet: The San Blas Islands, off the coast of Panama, may not offer your average Caribbean escape. But, that may be exactly why you’d want to go.
lead_paragraph: The street was empty when I locked the door at the inn and plopped myself down on the curb. It was 4:30 a.m., the air as still as slack water: a great time to be in Panama City. On the quiet, empty sidewalk I took inventory of everything I would need for the next few days: bug spray, sunscreen, snacks, bathing suit, shorts and lots and lots of water.
